- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper introduces a new numerical method for solving contact mechanics problems, which can be considered as a mathematical software development. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper focuses on the development and analysis of a numerical method for solving contact mechanics problems, which falls under the scope of numerical analysis. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper uses level set functions to represent boundaries and solve contact mechanics problems, which is a common technique in computational geometry. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering): The paper deals with the simulation of frictional multi-body contact problems, which is a common problem in mechanical engineering.
